This paper discusses a notation proposed by the VQEG working group SAM for analyzing subjective experiments in video quality assessment. The paper focuses on statistical analysis and methods, which suggests that it could belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category. The use of notation also involves information theory and communication, which could place it in the cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-category. The paper also deals with computer vision and image processing, which could make it relevant to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The consistent notation proposed in the paper could also have implications for human-computer interaction, which could place it in the cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) sub-category. Finally, the paper's focus on statistical analysis and methods could also make it relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
